cs.CV, cs.GR, cs.MM, cs.LG, cs.AI. 

The paper deals with increasing the spatial resolution of depth images using a deep fully convolutional network and a non-local variational method. This involves computer vision (CV) techniques such as image processing and image reconstruction. Therefore, cs.CV is the most likely sub-category. The paper also generates high-quality depth maps and color images using a physically based renderer, which falls under computer graphics (GR) and multimedia (MM). The use of deep learning techniques for optimization and training the network falls under machine learning (LG) and artificial intelligence (AI).
